sentences.english: The analyses show that for systems of few-degrees-of-freedom, there is little difference between the results of the above two methods.
sentences.chinese: 結果發現，對於少自由度系統來說，兩者相差不多。

sentences.english: The amount of time required by the old approach and the new approach is about the same.
sentences.chinese: 舊的方法要求的時間和新的相差不多。

sentences.english: The wealthy experience more mirth than the poor, but not much. Most people say they are happy, but perhaps that is because they are expected to be.
sentences.chinese: 有錢的人要比那些窮苦的人幸福，但是相差不多。

sentences.english: Their natures are much the same;
sentences.chinese: 他們的天性也都相差不多。

sentences.english: The cranial capacity of Neandertals was about as large as ours.
sentences.chinese: 尼安德特人的腦容量和智人相差不多。
